review_blob: Tap at lake and Irving. Copper gold with very thick white head. Very hoppy nose and taste. This is a classic hop heavy ipa, super solid. Still pretty one dimensional.
Tap at lake and Irving. Black with small white head. Roasted grain nose. Chocolate, malt, light medium body. Easy to drink for this style. Pretty good.
beer_name: Rush River Nevermore Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Tap at brewery with commonmac. Pint glass. Light gold with airy bubbly white head and good lacing. Sweet, slightly hoppy. Very pleasant and easy to drink. Some citrus, light body.
Bottle at kitty kat club. Hazy light orange yellow. Citrus nose. Sweet, orange, spicy. Spicy mouthfeel. Light and tasty, a great classic beer for the right moment.

Tap at yard house. Hazy murky orange rust color with thick foamy white head. Funky yeast nose. Sugar, yeast, funky full chewy flavor. A bit of a weird bitter sour combo, but an interesting Belgian approach to an imperial ipa.

Tap at devils advocate with commonmac. 10oz pour in tulip. Hazy gold with very thick white head and excellent lacing . Smells of sweet and hop balance. Tastes amazing. Much more tart and funky than most dipa, which is terrific. Hop and alcohol and bitter character come at the end. Great beer, right up my alley. This is what Ive been wanting a dipa to try .
UPDATED: APR 21, 2016

10oz pour at MacKenzie with commonmac. Nearly black with very thick foamy tan head and excellent lacing. Peanut butter chocolate nose. Sharp alcohol bite, then peanut butter, bitter chocolate, and lingering finish that could have been better. Peanut butter is weaker than expected. Medium to light body for this style, not creamy enough. Love the concept, but only like the beer.
beer_name: Ballast Point Victory at Sea - Peanut Butter

review_blob: Can at hells kitchen. Tastes like light grain. A bad beer but thats its charm. Needs to be very cold and in the right moment.

12oz bottle from total wine. Cola brown black with super thick creamy tan head. Smells of coffee and chocolate and spice, really nice. Full flavor of chocolate, slight coffee but less coffee than expected. Long lasting spice hit. Flavor goes for a long time with good complexity. Roasted bitter to finish with drying character. High alcohol flavor. Very good.
UPDATED: APR 15, 2016
beer_name: Central Waters Slinte Scottish Style Ale

review_blob: Tap at Butcher and boar with commonmac. Rated with a cold. Bumped pint. Dark red brown with really nice foamy white head. Malty nose. Taste is well balanced sugar, malt, and grain bitterness. Really well done, right down the middle carrying a bit of all the elements. Was worried it would be too malty but it wasnt. Tiny bit of roast and nuttiness. Nicely done.
beer_name: AleSmith Nut Brown Ale - All English (Draft Only)

review_blob: Tap at brewery with commonmac. Rated with a cold. Tulip glass. Black with bubbly white head with creamy cap. Sugary nose. Malt, then subtle chocolate, minor creaminess, and dry short finish. Medium body. Could be thicker with more creaminess. Tiny bit of smoke. Not bad.
beer_name: Lakes & Legends Oh, Lait: Milk Chocolate Porter

review_blob: Tap at brewery with commonmac. Rated with a cold. 13oz pour. Hazy gold with thick white head and good lacing. Strong citrus hop nose. Taste is nice funky citrus hop. A good but not overpowering bite. Medium, small, light body. Very drinkable and very good. Might be one of my favorites from these guys.
beer_name: Sisyphus The First Beer We Named

review_blob: Tap at Mccormicks in Wayzata. Dark Amber copper with medium white head and good lacing. Smells of Belgian yeast and sugar. Dark fruit, plum and prune. Good yeast. Nice sweetness and hidden alcohol. Amazing.
12oz bottle in dc. Black with small tan head. Smells sweet and stout like. Taste is chocolate, then smoky, then malty. Creamy dry mouth. Decent, not differentiated.
Bottle in dc. Light color . Light citrus and easy nose. Easy to drink, pleasant. Not a lot of complexity, but good for this style.
Bottle in dc. Copper with medium white head. Malt and hop balanced, some resin honey sweetness. Rich, full body. Not as good as their ipas but still decent

Tap at churchkey in DC. Dark copper plum with thick off white head. Dark fruit nose. Malty. Malty sweet and tangy grain. Slight caramel taste. Otherwise the malty grain dominates. Dark fruit is low in the taste. Finish is ok. Medium body. I wanted more layers and depth, but decent.
12oz bottle at birreria paradiso in dc. Light copper with medium white head. Citrus pine hop aroma. Resin hop with good citrus flavor. Like a west coast ipa. Very solid.

12oz can into glass at birreria paradiso in dc. Black with small off white head. Smells of strong chocolate creaminess. Taste is sweet, heavy chocolate. Medium light body for the style, could have been thicker and creamier. Still good.
beer_name: Hellbender North x Northeast Coffee Stout

review_blob: Tap at birreria paradiso in dc. Snifter. Orange gold with small white head. Smells like peach apricot skin. Sweet and fruity. Alcohol present but buried under sweetness. Oily mouthfeel. Tart slightly. Good for a fruit beer, but a fruit beer.

Tap at birreria paradiso in dc. Cola brown black with off white head. Grain nose with some roasted malt. Roasted sweet grain, small amount of smoke. Nice body, sweetness is the right amount. Well made beer.
Tap at Lukes lobster in DC. In Mason jar. Copper with small white head. Smells of cheap grain, and taste is similar. Sweet and some malt there. Pretty below average.
UPDATED: APR 8, 2016
beer_name: DuClaw 2011 H.E.R.O. Chocolate Peanut Butter Porter

review_blob: Tap at the fainting goat in DC. Hazy gold with medium white head. Citrus hop nose. Clean taste, crisp citrus hop. Really pleasant. Good beer.
Tap at sudhouse in dc. Hazy gold with medium white head. Grain nose. Taste is nice, sweet and spicy, good bite, mediocre grain finish. Pretty good.
Tap at right proper in DC. Light yellow with medium white head. Tropical nose. Very light, citrus, then spice. Thin body. Light and comfortable.

Tap at right proper. Light gold with small white head and good lacing. Herb spice citrus nose. Spicy bitter taste. Crisp, but with too much dry spice, maybe pepper, maybe too much floral. Refreshing and ok.

Tap at churchkey in DC. Snifter. Black with thick tan head. Strong alcohol stout nose. Big taste of creamy malt, chocolate, dark notes . Very soft an creamy. Velvet on the tongue. Strong alcohol taste. Finish is soft and clean.
Tap at churchkey in DC. Becher glass. Clear light copper with medium white head. Nice hop nose, clean. Direct taste, Sharp thin hop. Very professional. Good.

Tap at churchkey in DC. Becher glass, Gold with thick head and excellent lacing. Funky pine hop nose, strong. . Taste is slightly citrus, heavy resin, and fairly thick. Good amount of alcohol flavor. Solid .
Tap at 51st state in DC. Pint glass . Light amber with small white head. Light grain nose. Has a lager taste but with slightly more flavor and malt bite. Good for this style.
UPDATED: APR 6, 2016
UPDATED: APR 6, 2016

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: UPDATED: APR 4, 2016
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Adam from the Stone

review_blob: Bomber with commonmac during the final four. Dark plum black with lucious tan head. Smells boozy, sweet, dark fruit, tartness. Roasty, sweet, chocolate dark fruit. Long lasting complexity. Slightly bitter, drying and tarter mouthfeel than expected. Roasted malt sugar booze dominates. Not as creamy as I would have thought. Take care when riding this dragon.
UPDATED: APR 2, 2016
Tap at new bohemia in golden valley. Bumped pint glass. Dark copper with white head and good lacing. Subtle aroma. Malty throughout with decent spice hit. Soft body. Not bad.

Big bottle from Haskells with commonmac. Black with tan head. Looks great, but head and lacing dissipate Beautiful aroma, some tartness which is unusual. Rich, toffee coffee, high sweetness. Super smooth. Maybe a tinge of dark fruit tartness. Alcohol comes out more as it warms. Also get more sweet vanilla notes. This is a terrific stout.

Tap at new bohemia in uptown. 10oz goblet. Nearly black with medium off white head. Roasted starchy grain nose. Heavy roast taste, sugary sweetness, then quick malty finish. Prevalent alcohol. A porter with a slight twist, but not earth shattering.

Tap at new bohemia uptown with commonmac and samadouche. Bumped pint. Dark gold copper with nice thick white head and good lacing. Clean hop nose. Taste is fresh, bright, sharp, with a nice light bitter finish. These guys do killer ipas. Definitely reached safely on this one.

Big bottle from Haskells with commonmac as last beer of the opening weekend of March madness. 2014 bottle. Hazy plum with silky foamy pretty head. Belgian yeast and slightly tart nose. Very little alcohol aroma, maybe some raisin. Yeast funk, dark fruit, maybe a little light chocolate , sugar . A Belgian tasting strong ale. perfect mouthfeel with a tiny bit of bite and burn. Finish is comfortable and slightly warming. This is amazing. Makes me feel good.

12oz bottle with commonmac and samadouche during March madness . Dark gold with medium white head and good lacing. Resin nose. Sappy, sticky, hoppy. Fruit notes are subtle and underlying. Finish is pretty good. A decent one to have on hand.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob: Big bottle with commonmac during March madness. Black with medium tan head. Roasty nose. Taste is bandaid peat, roasted malt. Maybe some chocolate notes. Medium body. Wanted some different flavors in there. Ok.
12oz bottle with commonmac and samadouche. Gold with small white head. Citrus pine nose. Taste is fresh and bright citrus. Thin body. Finish is decent, with citrus bitterness. Pretty good.
UPDATED: APR 2, 2016
beer_name: Central Waters Brewers Reserve Bourbon Barrel Barleywine

review_blob: 12oz bottle from elevated with commonmac during March madness. Dark gold with small white head. Weird smell of beef stick. Must be the herbs. Oily and bitter. Atypical beer herbs throughout. Felt like I was drinking a roast. Pretty bitter for a saison. Kinda weird. Didnt really like it.
beer_name: Dogfish Head / Victory / Stone Saison du BUFF

review_blob: 12oz bottle from Princeton liquor with commonmac and Qponnagy during March madness. Light gold with medium white head. Very tart sour nose. Super sour. Lemon. Tart. Cant pull out a lot of other flavors. A clean taste, but you have to love sours.

12oz can from central ave liquor with commonmac and Qponnagy. Light copper with small white head. Resin hop nose and similar taste. Good body. Definitely strongly bitter. What Id expect from this style, but a little less sweet. Very good.
beer_name: Bent Paddle Hop Forest Double IPA
